#Text=Discover Your Authentic Self
#Text=It 's easy to get caught up in the values of society and , self-imposed morals then finding yourself someone completely different from how you started .
#Text=You find yourself wondering who you are and , what you want to be .
#Text=The problem is that you have no clue who you used to be or , how you used to think .
#Text=The best way to do that is to drop everything .
#Text=Steps
#Text=DROP EVERYTHING
#Text=Forget your hobbies
#Text=Forget your dreams
#Text=Forget your past itself
#Text=What is right and wrong to you ?
#Text=Some people think killing is always wrong no matter what .
#Text=They truly believe all life is sacred and should be protected at all costs .
#Text=Now did you really care about the indiiduals of 9/11 or the Tsunamis that hit Japan ?
#Text=If you do n't does that make you evil ?
#Text=You 're true self will know the answer in an instant so do n't get in it 's way .
#Text=Discover your virtues ; what do you put more stock in freedom or order ?
#Text=Create a list of controversies and pick a side off the top of your head then argue its morality based off of what your true self believes what is right and wrong .
#Text=A list of virtues-
#Text=Bravery- Opposite of cowardice
#Text=a virtue of someone who desire survival above all ; meaning to be with fear yet , face adversity
#Text=Wisdom- Opposite of ignorance
#Text=a virtue of someone seeking an easy life without hard descision ; meaning being able to discern an outcome when given information and , finding the best solution
#Text=Humility- Opposite of pride
#Text=a virtue of those without shame who live with utmost care of others perceptions ; meaning to withstand shame and , learn from it .
#Text=Find what you cannot do without .
#Text=In other words , love .
#Text=Be it money , family/friends , power or , even abstract concepts such as happiness and stories .
#Text=Do n't let anyone influence what you love absoulutely no one .
#Text=Even if you do everything else if you ca n't find your love you 'll never know who you are .
#Text=Unless you love nothing in which case you should find what you hate .
#Text=If you fail at both of those then find what brings you the most comfort .
#Text=Tips
#Text=If you struggle with morality think about those you admire be they real or fictional but , do n't copy them they 'll just give you hits about what you truly believe is right and wrong .
#Text=With your virtues
#Text=think about the kind of person you want to be in your ideal form .
#Text=Look up Benjamin Franklin 's virtues to see how he built his .
#Text=Remember that there is but one true good Knowledge and one true evil Ignorance .
#Text=Warnings
#Text=Just as scientists do n't allow foreign elements in their research
#Text=do n't let anyone influence you during this time
#Text=this is and has to be a solo mission
